All Implemented Interfaces:
Movable, Reproducible, Sleepable
public class Fish extends MarineHerbivore
The Fish class represents a marine herbivore species that consumes algae and moves swiftly in the water. It extends the MarineHerbivore class and includes specific behaviors for movement, eating, reproduction, predator detection, and sleeping.
